dip
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number: 1
Definition:to rid sheep and cattle of lice, keds, other parasites and fungi by placing in a spray, race, swim, pot or swim-through dip or by using pour-on.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
